House Resolution 423
By: Representatives Burns of the 159th and Hitchens of the 161st
A RESOLUTION
1 Congratulating Ernestine Hunter; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, this year, Ernestine Hunter will enjoy the rare distinction of celebrating her
3 100th birthday, entering the exclusive club of Georgia's centenarians; and
4 WHEREAS, Ernestine Hunter began her remarkable 42 year teaching career in 1942 at just
5 17 years old, serving as the only teacher in a one-room schoolhouse that educated children
6 aged 5 to 17; and
7 WHEREAS, she played a vital role in the education of Black students in Effingham County
8 during a time when high school education was largely inaccessible to them as they were
9 required to travel to Savannah or Statesboro until the establishment of Springfield Central
10 High School and Elementary School in 1956; and
11 WHEREAS, Ernestine Hunter demonstrated steadfast dedication to her students, adhering
12 to a regimented class schedule that included math, reading, English, spelling, and health
13 while also providing needed guidance and discipline; and
