14 WHEREAS, she taught thousands of students across many schools in Effingham County,
15 including Union Springs and Clyo, before concluding her distinguished career at Marlow
16 Elementary School in 1984; and
17 WHEREAS, Ernestine Hunter possesses the vast wisdom which only comes through
18 experience and the strength of character which is achieved through overcoming the many
19 challenges of life; and
20 WHEREAS, she has witnessed a dramatic change in the world over the course of her
21 lifetime, and we salute her contribution to its progress by her own hard work, good
22 citizenship, and commitment to the youth of this state; and
23 WHEREAS, by the example Ernestine Hunter has made of her life, she makes this world a
24 better place in which to live, and it is only fitting and proper that she be appropriately
25 recognized during this very special and memorable time.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
27 the members of this body congratulate Ernestine Hunter upon the remarkable occasion of her
28 100th birthday and extend the most sincere best wishes for continued health and happiness.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
30 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
31 Ernestine Hunter.
